Source: gnuais
Section: hamradio
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruben Undheim <ruben.undheim@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 9), cmake, libasound2-dev, libmysqlclient-dev, libpulse-dev, libcurl4-openssl-dev, libgtk-3-dev, libosmgpsmap-1.0-dev (>= 1.0.2), libsoup2.4-dev
Standards-Version: 3.9.5
Homepage: http://gnuais.sourceforge.net/ 

Package: gnuais
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: GNU Automatic Identification System receiver
 A tool for demodulating and decoding AIS messages using the line input of the
 sound card. AIS messages are transmitted by marine vessels and contain their
 position, velocity and other interesting information. The messages may be
 saved to a mysql-database, forwarded as NMEA packets or uploaded to an AIS web
 service. 

Package: gnuais-dbg
Architecture: any
Section: debug
Priority: extra
Depends: gnuais (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: GNU Automatic Identification System receiver (debug symbols)
 A tool for demodulating and decoding AIS messages using the line input of the
 sound card. AIS messages are transmitted by marine vessels and contain their
 position, velocity and other interesting information. The messages may be
 saved to a mysql-database, forwarded as NMEA packets or uploaded to an AIS web
 service. 
 .
 This package contains the debugging symbols for gnuais.

Package: gnuaisgui
Architecture: any
Depends: gnuais (= ${binary:Version}), ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: GUI for GNU Automatic Identification System receiver
 This GUI plots the vessels that are received by gnuais in an OpenStreetMap
 GUI. 
 .
 gnuais must be running in the background for gnuaisgui to be 
 functional.

Package: gnuaisgui-dbg
Architecture: any
Section: debug
Priority: extra
Depends: gnuaisgui (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: GUI for GNU Automatic Identification System receiver (debug symbols)
 This GUI plots the vessels that are received by gnuais in an OpenStreetMap
 GUI.
 .
 This package contains the debugging symbols for gnuaisgui.
